summary: Test DNF install/downgrade/reinstall behaviour for artifact plugin
test: ./test.sh

description: |
    Outer beakerlib test that detects the current distro, picks the matching
    container image, copies the inner fmf tree from data/ into a temp directory,
    and runs the 10 DNF behaviour scenarios via an inner tmt run.

    Scenarios covered (run inside the inner container):
      01 - Fresh install from artifact repo
      02 - Upgrade: older version installed, artifact has newer
      03 - Downgrade: newer version installed, explicit NVRA
      04 - Same NVRA, unknown origin: dnf install is a no-op for origin
      05 - Same NVRA, unknown origin: dnf reinstall fixes origin
      06 - Transitive dep downgrade (--allow-downgrade on DNF5, auto on DNF4)
      07 - --repo / --from-repo flag behaviour
      08 - Obsoletes + --allowerasing
      09 - Full two-command pattern (install + reinstall)
      10 - DNF4-only: --allow-downgrade flag must not exist

tag+:
  - provision-only
  - provision-container

require+:
  - beakerlib
  - tmt+plugins
  - rpm-build
  - createrepo_c

adjust:
  - when: distro != centos and distro != fedora
    enabled: false
    because: Tests target dnf4 (CentOS Stream 9) and dnf5 (Fedora 43+)
